Foot and mouth disease, Russia
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 29 Nov 2016 from Dr Evgeny Nepoklonov, deputy head, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance, Ministry of Agriculture, Moscow, Russia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 22 Nov 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 26 Nov 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 28 May 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Sredneargunsk, Krasanokamensky, [Zabaykalsky Krai]
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Nov 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 481 / 113 / 0 / - / 0
Sheep/goats / 260 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 23.5 / 0 / 0 / **
Sheep/goats / 0 / 0 / - / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; disinfection/disinfestation; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/ or protection zone; zoning; no treatment of affected animals;
Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division: Zabaykalsky Krai
Species / Total vaccinated
Cattle / 2376
Sheep/goats / 2231
Measures to be applied: modified stamping out

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
All-Russian Research Institute for Animal Health (FGBI-ARRIAH) (OIE's reference laboratory) / Cattle / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 26 Nov 2016 / Positive
All-Russian Research Institute for Animal Health (FGBI-ARRIAH) (OIE's reference laboratory) / Cattle / complement fixation test (CFT) / 26 Nov 2016 / Positive
All-Russian Research Institute for Animal Health (FGBI-ARRIAH) (OIE's reference laboratory) / Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 26 Nov 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Information from the WRLFMD (Pirbright) [World Reference Laboratory for Foot-and-Mouth Disease] web page, indicates that samples obtained from the Zabaykalsky territory in July and August 2010, and in February 2014, were FMDV type O - topotype SEA, and FMDV type O - topotype ME-SA respectively (see http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/asia/rus.htm.

Vaccination as a response to the outbreak has been applied. Any details on the type of vaccine used would be useful and will hopefully be provided in follow-up reports.

See relevant comments by Mod.AS in posting 20161126.4656143. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4663033,56841.]
